SF has always been a life-giving city to me.
I’m just thankful to be here with good people, good coffee & good food.
Cheers to 31 y’all. 
Time to figure out who I really am.

Ohhh I love the stability a solid heel-hook can give 😮‍💨 - rock climbing is so fun. If anyone wants to come with me lmk.
@senderone_lax

Did a little birthday trip up to SF and got to climb this sweet 5.10b that had a sweeet traverse across to a stalagmite 30ft up!
#climbinglife #rockclimbers #sanfrancisco #birthdaytrip #climbingbeta #rocks

Went out to Joshua Tree last weekend and was able to lead my first 5.9 on “Sexy Grandma”💪🏼😃 aaaand then I had to navigate a tricky miscalculation on a slab wall in Echo Cove that tested my confidence in myself and my skills to traverse and down-climb. 
I left this weekend feeling very proud of myself and @manderrss__ for what we accomplished in the desert! Can’t wait for the next trip!

Clips of life and people I love🙂
Life can be hard, can leave you with lots of questions and wondering/wandering. It helps to have some solid people around you to remind you of what’s important.
I don’t have things figured out at all, but im moving forward.

JJ Braves first tour y’all!
So happy to be in PNW again!

⚠️PDX friends: Make sure to show up early because we actually go on-stage at 7pm tonight!⚠️
Swipe for tour memories, including Hotel Band Practice, Mars Attacks the venue, and Oregon rainy drives 🤘🏼

SEATTLE, WA - we are on our way north to see you tonight. 😄 let’s get weird.
Also we neeed to say Thank you to Portland for a warm loving welcome to your town!
We made new friends and will 100% be back in the future. Y’all made us feel like family here 😊🙏🏼
Join us Tuesday 12/5 for a night of Throwback Rock tunes from @jjbravesofficial 🎸 8:30pm 🥃 drink @gryphonandgrain and enjoy the music 🤘🏼

This tour has definitely blown all of our expectations 🤯 we are incredibly thankful to all the venues and bands we’ve played with this last week. We are so lucky to have made new friends and spend time with old ones.
We cannot wait to return to the PNW

This video represents only a sliver of joy shared on this tour! 😁 Our first time playing “THE CIRCLE COMPLETE” outside of our home of Los Angeles surpassed all expectations 🤯 
Sometimes you just need to put on some music and dance celebrate in the hotel room cause your was a certified SUCCESS 😎
It’s hard to believe how far things have come from our first rehearsals earlier this year. Thank you to everyone who has come across our music and seen us play live. 2024 only holds amazing things for and for you!
See you next year homies 🤘🏼
